    {
      "start": 93.2,
      "end": 93.76,
      "text": "어기도 어기."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.98,
      "end": 99.86,
      "text": "자, 체코 체코에게 처음으로 이 성공을 안겨준 작품이라고 말씀을 드렸었잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.06,
      "end": 100.2,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.2,
      "end": 107.74,
      "text": "But I heard that Seagull was a famous disaster when it was first performed in 1896, 그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.84,
      "end": 111.86,
      "text": "Yes, it was infamous, very infamous."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.98,
      "end": 112.48,
      "text": "아, 그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.68,
      "end": 116.74,
      "text": "In theater history, this event has become an infamous event."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.84,
      "end": 120.76,
      "text": "So people who know theater and know plays, they know about this."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.76,
      "end": 126.6,
      "text": "그래요, 초연된 직후에는 반응이 영 안 좋았다라는 이야기입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.6,
      "end": 128.12,
      "text": "So it was a disaster."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.12,
      "end": 132.5,
      "text": "The audience were not very happy."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.14,
      "end": 135.78,
      "text": "They booed, like really loud."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.4,
      "end": 136.72,
      "text": "Boo!"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.12,
      "end": 138.0,
      "text": "Oh, 어떡해."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.04,
      "end": 139.22,
      "text": "They jeered the actors."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.54,
      "end": 141.02,
      "text": "They made fun of the actors."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.3,
      "end": 142.32,
      "text": "They booed the actors."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.9,
      "end": 144.56,
      "text": "The actors lost their confidence."
    },
    {
      "start": 145.38,
      "end": 147.84,
      "text": "Many of them even forgot their lines."
    },
    {
      "start": 147.84,
      "end": 148.82,
      "text": "아, 그럼요."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.96,
      "end": 156.02,
      "text": "이 공연 중에 관객들이 막 우우우, 이렇게 야유를 퍼부으면 과연 배우의 입장에서 어땠을까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.24,
      "end": 157.0,
      "text": "기눈 들어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.36,
      "end": 158.84,
      "text": "상상만으로도 너무 끔찍해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 159.04,
      "end": 159.26,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 159.76,
      "end": 166.9,
      "text": "And back then they had a prompter, not a computer, but a guy who held up like their lines on paper."
    },
    {
      "start": 166.9,
      "end": 169.84,
      "text": "And they couldn't even focus on those."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.58,
      "end": 173.38,
      "text": "They lost track, forgot their lines."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.3,
      "end": 178.3,
      "text": "And Mr. Chekov himself, he was in the audience."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.44,
      "end": 179.76,
      "text": "He was watching the play."
    },
    {
      "start": 180.04,
      "end": 183.6,
      "text": "But during the second act, he just walked off."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.92,
      "end": 186.36,
      "text": "He walked out of the theater and he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.52,
      "end": 190.22,
      "text": "I'm never going to write another play again as long as I live."
    },
    {
      "start": 190.68,
      "end": 192.86,
      "text": "너무 좌절을 했겠군요, 그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 192.86,
      "end": 193.46,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 193.8,
      "end": 196.04,
      "text": "So the first performance was a disaster."
    },
    {
      "start": 196.24,
      "end": 199.76,
      "text": "But one person, a famous playwright, a director,"
    },
    {
      "start": 200.1,
      "end": 204.16,
      "text": "he liked the play and he wanted to direct it again."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.34,
      "end": 210.64,
      "text": "So he went to the Moscow Art Theater, which is a brand new fancy theater in Moscow."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.94,
      "end": 216.76,
      "text": "And in 1898, he put on the same play, The Seagull, and it got rave reviews."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.0,
      "end": 217.18,
      "text": "Really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 217.18,
      "end": 221.0,
      "text": "It got a great reception and it restored Chekov's confidence."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.42,
      "end": 221.72,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.72,
      "end": 224.96,
      "text": "And he went on to launch a great playwriting career."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.22,
      "end": 226.18,
      "text": "Wow, that was a good twist."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.34,
      "end": 227.62,
      "text": "It was a great twist."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.86,
      "end": 229.0,
      "text": "Wow, 다행이네요."
